stimulus:
The Illusion Game

In this reaction-time game, you will need to be as fast as possible and make correct responses by resisting different visual illusions.

We will show you examples of each illusion before each block.

Remember, your goal is to be as fast and accurate as possible. Good luck!

Part 1

In this part, two horizontal red lines will appear one above the other.

Your task is to select which line is longer in size as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the surrounding black lines!

Press the UP or the DOWN arrow to indicate where is the longest red line.

In this example, the correct answer is the UP arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

3378

Can you do better in the next illusion?

Part 2

In this part, two vertical grey rectangles will appear side by side.

Your task is to tell which rectangle is of a lighter color, as fast as you can, and without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the background color!

Press the LEFT or the RIGHT arrow to indicate which side has the lighter rectangle.

In this example, the correct answer is the LEFT arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

3559

Can you do better in the next illusion?

In this part, one vertical red line will appear in a square.

Your task is to tell which direction is the red line leaning, as fast as you can, and without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the black square!

Press the LEFT or the RIGHT arrow to indicate the direction where the red line is leaning.

In this example, the correct answer is the LEFT arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

Can you do better in the next illusion?
